page.title: 08THE VILLAGE OF KEYINGHAM
page.content: Keyingham has been split into two halves, with the A1033 Hull to Withernsea road being the dividing line. The north side of the village being more developed with residential housing and shops. The church of England is on this side and the village hall, much used by the many village organisations. The south side of Keyingham, while having much less houses, does have shops along the main street, the two schools, both doctors surgeries and the Methodist church which allows its hall to be used as a child welfare clinic once a month. There is also a playing field which is shared by the junior school and local residents. Once again a place with a sense of community, with most people knowing each other and choosing to live there to sample country life rather than living there for necessity
